               <interpGrp>
                  <interp xml:id="ana_007" source="ph_007"><!-- link to nanopub -->
                     <desc>
                        In her memoirs (<rs type="lit_work" ref="#lit_work_id_162">"Auden in Kirchstetten"</rs> 210, <ref target="acdh:amp-transcript__0062.xml">"The Years in Austria"</ref> 14-15), <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_2">Stella Musulin</rs> refers to her own previous letter to Berlin, in which she had mentioned <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_70">Brian Bunting</rs>'s non-fiction book <rs type="lit_work" ref="#lit_work_id_72">The Rise of the South African Reich</rs> in relation to the issue of torture.
